    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 6.26,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 7.2,
      "end": 12.3,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 13.66,
      "end": 17.08,
      "text": "ASOP's Fables, The Bear and The Fox.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 18.72,
      "end": 25.36,
      "text": "A bear was once bragging about his generous feelings and saying how refined he was compared with other animals.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 25.36,
      "end": 30.02,
      "text": "There is, in fact, a tradition that a bear will never touch a dead body.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 30.88,
      "end": 35.26,
      "text": "A fox who heard him talking in this strain smiled and said,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 35.78,
      "end": 43.26,
      "text": "My friend, when you are hungry, I only wish you would confine your attention to the dead and leave the living alone.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 44.12,
      "end": 47.12,
      "text": "A hypocrite deceives no one but himself.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 48.24,
      "end": 51.14,
      "text": "End of The Bear and The Fox.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
